showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2922.topic&index=23>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: coupla uses come to mind</span><hr size=1> Have you tried the skill yet? :)<br>
<br>
The usefulness of the skill will come from the creative uses people find for it. It wasn't all that long ago that people called poisons completely useless. Mythic nudged them right along in the right direction.<br>
<br>
Besides disguise, which should have been in 5 months ago, Mythic has done a fine job of making sure each new addition to assassins had a use. All the creative assassins found a niche use for every skill. Climb, safe fall, evade, poisons... all have their limited uses. Shadowrun is no different.<br>
<br>
Is Shadowrun inferior to Vanish and Viper? Well, I think it's Inferior to Viper, but superior to Vanish. Let's be honest, Nightshades needed a little damage output help. Unlike Vanish and Shadowrun, Viper still requires that the user have a high envenom spec to take full benefits from the skill.<br>
<br>
Shadowrun and Vanish rely upon having a high stealth spec... any assassin without a high stealth spec isn't much of an assassin.<br>
<br>
Shadowrun is going to allow Shadowblades in doing hit and runs. Something they already do a devestating job at.<br>
<br>
Vanish is going to allow Infiltrators to hide when archers or casters are smacking them around.<br>
<br>
Viper is going to allow Nightshades to kill their targets without having to stay around for the death.<br>
<br>
I currently hit, run, sprint, stealth, and pray... imagine if you could run, sprint, stealth and keep running. That's what shadowrun will likely be. If it's a 30 second stealthed sprint every 5 minutes, Shadowblades are going to be a total pain in the butt to kill--worse than they already are.<br>
<br>
Some folks have suggested stealth sprinting to get in position, but I think this skill will very much be the get-out-of-death free card I've always wanted as an assassin.<br>
 <p><p style="text-align: right; font-size: 80%; font-family: Verdana">Jalena! Nightshade of Percival<br><i>Danger calls; it intoxicates. Beyond the walls real excitement waits.<br>Adreneline rush--dance along the ledge. Forbidden touch--kiss the razor's edge.</i></p>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uxumten.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xumten</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/29/02 7:52:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2922.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A few I plan to try...</span><hr size=1> Just basing on the small info available, and when it actually works, I see myself using it both offensively and defensively.<br>
<br>
Im very excited to see what this skill does. Im a critblade, and my playstyle is basically one-shotting all the wounded. And vs Albion and their horde of Smite Clerics(read: clerics who dont heal) there are ALWAYS plenty of wounded Albions running around. <br>
<br>
Like it was mentioned... speeding in... one-shot... and keep going. How many times have we seen that caster or almost dead tank sitting... we move in only to have them stand up/get healed right before we get there? Shadowrun will probably allow us to strike much faster. <br>
<br>
Using it to speed away after a One-shot. Probably will be its most common use. I already one-shot players with 5+ enemy around and get away 90% of the time. This just increased my chances.<br>
<br>
And also using it to speed away out of detection. Picking off the wounded means Im behind enemy lines 99% of the time. The whole Critblade vs other assassin debate is pointless to me because if you detect me you win. <br>
<br>
Scaling Keep Walls. Depending on how fast this skill is... this may be a very valuable skill to scale up fast and over.. possibly allowing us to get by enemy assasins camping the climb spot before the &quot;detect lag&quot; kicks in. <br>
<br>
While the majority of Shadowblades feel Shadowrun is useless, I'm actually VERY VERY VERY excited about this skill.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=2922.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=2922.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2922.topic&index=24><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=2922.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.threadControl?topicID=2922.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2922.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2922.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies">Training Studio<option 